 sensenum=\"2\"><span class=\"sensetop\" hclass=\"sensetop\" htag=\"span\"><span class=\"labels\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"labels\">(disapproving)</span></span> <span class=\"def\" hclass=\"def\" htag=\"span\">an extremely excited and <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/exaggerated#exaggerated_sng_2\" title=\"exaggerated definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">exaggerated</span></a> way of behaving or reacting to an event</span><ul class=\"examples\" hclass=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">the usual media hysteria that surrounds royal visits</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">public hysteria about AIDS</span></li></ul><div class=\"collapse\" htag=\"div\" hclass=\"collapse\"><span class=\"unbox\" unbox=\"extra_examples\" id=\"hysteria_unbox_3\"><span class=\"box_title\">Extra Examples</span><ul class=\"examples\" hclass=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">the hysteria whipped up by some newspapers</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">Unnecessary anxiety has been caused by media hysteria and misinformation.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">Some parts of the media are creating hysteria and exaggerating an important issue.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">There is still so much hysteria surrounding the issue.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">public hysteria about the bombings</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">hysteria over AIDS</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">the hysteria that swept through the country</span></li></ul></span></div><div class=\"collapse\" hclass=\"collapse\" htag=\"div\"><span class=\"unbox\" unbox=\"snippet\" id=\"hysteria_unbox_4\"><span class=\"box_title\">Oxford Collocations Dictionary</span><span class=\"body\"><span class=\"unbox\">adjective</span><ul class=\"collocs_list\